1
00:00:00,567 --> 00:00:02,986
That's what gets me excited
to come to work every day

2
00:00:02,987 --> 00:00:04,338
and do the work we do.

3
00:00:04,338 --> 00:00:07,608
To introduce Americans
to Korean culture and Korean food.

4
00:00:08,141 --> 00:00:12,980
It's cool to be a part of a movement
to create a new food craze,

5
00:00:12,980 --> 00:00:15,582
a food wave in the US.

6
00:00:15,582 --> 00:00:18,118
We have the mandu, the mini wantons.

7
00:00:18,118 --> 00:00:21,054
Those are all staples within our household.

8
00:00:21,054 --> 00:00:24,658
We want to make having Asian at home
a weekly occasion.

9
00:00:31,665 --> 00:00:34,371
My interest was sparked in K-food

10
00:00:34,372 --> 00:00:37,037
by having the opportunity
to work on the bibigo brand

11
00:00:37,037 --> 00:00:39,673
and to try the whole entire portfolio.

12
00:00:39,673 --> 00:00:42,543
I think K-food is so unique

13
00:00:42,543 --> 00:00:47,681
but it's also rooted in
a really known form to Americans.

14
00:00:47,681 --> 00:00:50,603
But we are able to bring a very Korean flavor,

15
00:00:50,604 --> 00:00:54,321
and that Korean authenticity and boldness.

16
00:00:54,321 --> 00:00:57,090
We have a pizza chef in the Twin Cities Campus

17
00:00:57,090 --> 00:00:59,026
named Anne Kim, who's Korean American.

18
00:00:59,026 --> 00:01:02,296
When she started adding
Korean ingredients to her pizzas,

19
00:01:02,296 --> 00:01:04,798
it showed me what K-flavor can bring

20
00:01:04,798 --> 00:01:07,067
even to a dish as American as pizza.

21
00:01:07,067 --> 00:01:11,638
But maybe interested in things like kimchi
and things like gochujang

22
00:01:11,638 --> 00:01:14,541
in bold flavors that I hadn't experienced before.

23
00:01:14,541 --> 00:01:17,611
I had an opportunity
very early on in my experience

24
00:01:17,611 --> 00:01:21,682
to go to Fullerton and the Beaumont plant.

25
00:01:21,682 --> 00:01:24,682
And that was an amazing opportunity

26
00:01:24,683 --> 00:01:28,989
to learn about bibigo
on the front end of my experience.

27
00:01:28,989 --> 00:01:33,627
Getting the chance to see the growth
that was happening with our dumplings

28
00:01:33,627 --> 00:01:39,032
and the amazing trajectory
that CJ and bibigo were on

29
00:01:39,032 --> 00:01:43,437
was an inspiration to me to want to be
a part of this company and that journey.

30
00:01:43,437 --> 00:01:47,603
And at the scale of the US,
especially our younger generation,

31
00:01:47,604 --> 00:01:52,145
adopting Korean food, Asian cuisine
is at a really high rate.

32
00:01:52,145 --> 00:01:54,781
Like ramyun is the new mac and cheese.

33
00:01:54,781 --> 00:01:57,922
I think the US market is right
for continued growth,

34
00:01:57,923 --> 00:02:01,388
both in the flavors, the food,
and most importantly, the experience.

35
00:02:04,391 --> 00:02:08,362
As Americans,
we don't always love the spiciest of food,

36
00:02:08,362 --> 00:02:10,951
but we need to understand it to do our job well,

37
00:02:10,952 --> 00:02:15,352
to incorporate Korean flavor in the right way,
in the most authentic way,

38
00:02:15,353 --> 00:02:17,638
to make sure that our products
are right for the consumers.

39
00:02:17,638 --> 00:02:19,504
I would say in Food Service,

40
00:02:19,505 --> 00:02:22,142
we have an obsession with the Gochujang Sauce.

41
00:02:22,142 --> 00:02:26,747
I think my team, even my family at home,

42
00:02:26,747 --> 00:02:30,984
it's become almost more prevalent in our house
than ketchup.

43
00:02:30,984 --> 00:02:35,589
My husband literally puts Gochujang
on everything.

44
00:02:35,589 --> 00:02:37,958
He makes soup with Gochujang,

45
00:02:37,958 --> 00:02:41,094
he puts it on pretty much every food
that we've made

46
00:02:41,094 --> 00:02:42,663
and I'm not even exaggerating.

47
00:02:42,663 --> 00:02:46,009
The way that I introduced my parents
to Korean flavor

48
00:02:46,010 --> 00:02:51,605
was through a recipe
that combined Gochujang and noodles.

49
00:02:51,605 --> 00:02:54,541
So I made them this dish,
which is from The New York Times,

50
00:02:54,541 --> 00:02:57,344
so playing with flavor as a Gochujang-base sauce,

51
00:02:57,344 --> 00:02:59,713
a little bit of honey
for some additional sweetness,

52
00:02:59,713 --> 00:03:03,330
and I think that opened their eyes
to a different world of flavor

53
00:03:03,331 --> 00:03:05,485
that we've been living in
for the last few of years here.

54
00:03:05,485 --> 00:03:09,798
And what's something in Food Service
we've been exploring a lot

55
00:03:09,799 --> 00:03:15,882
is how do you fuse K-flavor
with regular kind of American staples,

56
00:03:15,883 --> 00:03:20,400
whether that's hot dogs or barbeque.

57
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:23,170
It can come through in a lot of different ways.

58
00:03:23,170 --> 00:03:28,803
Incorporating K-food
into what we do and how we eat

59
00:03:28,804 --> 00:03:32,776
has been one of the most exciting pieces
about being part of CJ.

60
00:03:35,472 --> 00:03:37,945
One of the things
that I've been really passionate about

61
00:03:37,966 --> 00:03:39,576
over the last year or so

62
00:03:39,576 --> 00:03:42,680
is building our e-commerce presence.

63
00:03:42,680 --> 00:03:47,551
In fact, we had a great campaign this December
called "12 Days of Giftsmas,"

64
00:03:47,551 --> 00:03:51,060
where two of our influencer fans

65
00:03:51,061 --> 00:03:55,426
received 12 gifts from bibigo
to celebrate their fandom.

66
00:03:55,427 --> 00:03:58,429
And with that, a ton of engagement.

67
00:03:58,429 --> 00:04:02,733
We saw sales lift
and we were able to continue to connect.

68
00:04:02,733 --> 00:04:05,536
Over the last year,
we've really had a ton of growth,

69
00:04:05,536 --> 00:04:08,205
particularly on Amazon,
but more broadly with e-commerce.

70
00:04:08,205 --> 00:04:10,174
We'll be launching on TikTok Shop.

71
00:04:10,174 --> 00:04:12,142
The biggest store in the US is Walmart.

72
00:04:12,142 --> 00:04:15,245
Walmart is a customer
that is very, very, very tough.

73
00:04:15,245 --> 00:04:18,449
We had tried for a few years and we had failed.

74
00:04:18,449 --> 00:04:20,751
So we decided last year to change our approach.

75
00:04:20,751 --> 00:04:21,811
So what we did,

76
00:04:21,812 --> 00:04:25,744
we invited the buyer out from Arkansas,
where their headquarters is,

77
00:04:25,745 --> 00:04:27,491
to LA, to Los Angeles.

78
00:04:27,491 --> 00:04:29,893
And we took her into the market

79
00:04:29,893 --> 00:04:36,319
and we went to authentic stores
to open her eyes to the world of Korean food,

80
00:04:36,320 --> 00:04:38,969
to the world of K-flavor, to the world of bibigo.

81
00:04:38,969 --> 00:04:43,507
Seeing a whole wall of bibigo kimchi
was inspirational for her.

82
00:04:43,507 --> 00:04:45,529
So that was a new approach that we took.

83
00:04:45,530 --> 00:04:46,728
Last year at Walmart,

84
00:04:46,729 --> 00:04:50,880
we grew the number of items in Walmart
by almost 100%.

85
00:04:50,881 --> 00:04:53,917
So we almost doubled the number of items
that we had in that store.

86
00:04:53,917 --> 00:04:58,155
And that required us taking a different approach
than we had in the past.

87
00:05:01,158 --> 00:05:05,462
In fact, nearly 70% of people say
they love Asian food,

88
00:05:05,462 --> 00:05:09,833
but over half of them are still going
to a restaurant as their first option.

89
00:05:09,833 --> 00:05:10,806
And so in the US,

90
00:05:10,807 --> 00:05:14,304
a lot of consumers have "Taco Tuesday"
or they have pizza on Friday.

91
00:05:14,304 --> 00:05:17,908
We want to make having Asian at home
a weekly occasion.

92
00:05:17,908 --> 00:05:21,145
Putting Korean food in the rotation,

93
00:05:21,145 --> 00:05:27,584
I think it has earned the right
to have a day on the American meal planning.

94
00:05:27,584 --> 00:05:31,588
More and more authentic Korean food represented.

95
00:05:31,588 --> 00:05:33,791
Flavor is becoming increasingly global.

96
00:05:33,791 --> 00:05:36,024
bibigo and Korean food in general

97
00:05:36,025 --> 00:05:39,429
have proven they can win
even in a global environment.

98
00:05:39,430 --> 00:05:42,066
This is some of the best relationships
with our retail partners.

99
00:05:42,066 --> 00:05:46,337
And we have a really solid understanding
of the US consumer.

100
00:05:46,337 --> 00:05:50,090
And so that powered
with all of the amazing R&D work

101
00:05:50,091 --> 00:05:51,507
that comes from Blossom Park,

102
00:05:51,508 --> 00:05:55,145
as well as just the great understanding
of the brand

103
00:05:55,145 --> 00:05:57,064
and everything that's happening in Seoul.

104
00:05:57,065 --> 00:05:59,831
Those are a great mix for us to continue

105
00:05:59,832 --> 00:06:04,121
to expand distribution and consumer awareness
in the US market.

106
00:06:04,121 --> 00:06:09,301
And so having now the mindset,
the resources, the expertise

107
00:06:09,302 --> 00:06:12,396
to bring our long range plan
and our vision to life,

108
00:06:12,396 --> 00:06:14,320
we can't do it alone

109
00:06:14,321 --> 00:06:16,118
saying we're going to have a weekly occasion,

110
00:06:16,119 --> 00:06:19,636
we're gonna dethrone "Taco Tuesday"
with "Asian Thursday."

111
00:06:19,636 --> 00:06:23,707
We'll play a key role in bringing
that K-wave to life in the US.

112
00:06:23,707 --> 00:06:25,476
And it's the perfect company to do it

113
00:06:25,476 --> 00:06:31,448
because of the Korean heritage
and lifestyle that CJ brings to life.

114
00:06:31,448 --> 00:06:33,684
And so my vision and my hope is that

115
00:06:33,684 --> 00:06:38,222
we can bring these cuisines and these products
to more people who enjoy them with other people.

116
00:06:48,799 --> 00:06:52,670
Not one versus the other, we are one team.

117
00:06:52,670 --> 00:06:55,877
And we do need to be aggressive in the market.

118
00:06:55,878 --> 00:07:00,144
But we have to do it in a way that
we bring people together

119
00:07:00,144 --> 00:07:02,864
and we get the job done as one team.

120
00:07:02,865 --> 00:07:04,638
And that's what's exciting to see.

121
00:07:04,639 --> 00:07:07,316
These cultures come together at the end of the day.

122
00:07:07,317 --> 00:07:10,854
I'm inspired by further embracing
the "who we prove it" mindset

123
00:07:10,854 --> 00:07:12,589
as we have in pizza historically,

124
00:07:12,589 --> 00:07:15,693
and using that mindset
to fuel our growth into the future.

125
00:07:15,693 --> 00:07:19,363
Yeah, we're really excited
to take the information that we've learned

126
00:07:19,363 --> 00:07:20,764
and start to embrace
the "who we prove it" mindset

127
00:07:20,764 --> 00:07:23,867
and some of the hunter mindset concepts
that we've been talking about

128
00:07:23,867 --> 00:07:25,569
and introduce them to our team.

